Title: FIFA 19 | Official Reveal Trailer with UEFA Champions League
Comment:
Greetings,

I have such an odd problem with the demo. Unlike almost all folks across the Internet saying the game is way too fast, my game conversely feels super slow. I have no fucking idea what could be causing this.

I have been testing the demo on a 5-year old notebook. I also tested FIFA 18 demo right before the installation of this year's demo and i did not encounter any issues related to the game speed on that. But FIFA 19 demo is somehow absolutely slow. I do not refer to the lag, choppiness, bad frame rates but the pace of the game is incredibly slow which is rather frustrating.

Either adjusted to medium or low options, frame rates roll around 30 except the close cam moments an cutscenes (nothing painful unless i choose high or above i mean).

The game executable is added to Nvidia Control Panel, high performance selected on both this stuff and the notebook battery performance options. I also switched to lower values on both things but still the game does flow so slowly! i can not enjoy the game due to such awkwardness!

Comment:
Dear EA, I will not be buying fifa this year or any subsequent years until it is actually a new game worth buying. Personally, I find it insulting that all you do is repackage the same gear year after year, and I for one have had enough.

Career mode (both managerial and be a pro), the game mode that everybody loves and the basis of your success, has been abandoned to focus on you're cash cow, ultimate team. It's a disgrace. I can't remember the last significant change to a career mode for years and it's not like there isn't any ideas, just flick through the comments on this video and you'll see thousands of valid ideas that would make a huge difference to the experience. Here are but a few:
- longer career mode 
- more managerial responsibilities (on and off the pitch)
- kit changes every season
- the ability to play online career mode with friends
- the ability to sign and negotiate contracts in be a pro
- the ability to talk with other teams in be a pro
- the ability to come on as a sub in be a pro

The list is endless...

The addition of the champions league, while welcome, isn't good enough. It's the same game with a better logo and music.

I know I am only one person and you'll only be losing ¬£50-¬£60 but I refuse to put another penny towards the effortless millions you generate conning everybody with the same game year upon year.

i have done some intensive research on Fifa 18 , which show me that . 
You should only buy Fifa 19 to enjoy on an single player level , Unless you're a very competitive gamer or pro-gamer.

Even the way interceptions and tackling are executed in Fifa 18 Online modes , where you're needed to push more than 1 button while trying to press another ,
Almost impossible with the normal console controller.
A lot more issues were found with Fifa 18 Online mode , but hopefully they have been found and fixed for Fifa 19 .
So if you are thinking about enjoying this game , Remember the online mode is VERY competitive .
Sticking with the single player modes or against your friend and you can't ask for a more realistic and fun football experience on the virtual level with hours of fun .

Title: FIFA 19 | Official Reveal Trailer with UEFA Champions League
FIFA 19 | Official Reveal Trailer with UEFA Champions League
Comment: My first football game was FIFA 09. I really enjoyed FIFA till FIFA 14. I had played PES 11 but I really didn't enjoyed it that much. After that I started playing PES again (PES 15) and I have been a PES fan ever since. Tbh the past few FIFAs have been really disappointing. FIFA has been running purely on hype for some time now. It has great presentation, marketing and licences but the gameplay is widely inferior to PES. The last decade has been great for FIFA but it has lost its way. FUT was an interesting concept when it was introduced but EA has made it into a cash cow which is designed to make you spend on cards. The main reason behind all these is EA. They are a company who are too focused on making money and have forgotten what make video games great in the first place. That's why nobody like them anymore. if you have made it this far you must be thinking I am biased towards PES, but in reality I am just a football fan who likes good football games and just thought about speaking my mind. The PES team at the least have some plan and have been making a lot of improvements since Adam Bhatti took over. They decided not to renew the UCL/EL contract and instead focus their resources elsewhere. That's a drastic step but I think most PES fans support it. UCL had just become a skin at one point and we want to see the game continue to make great strides. Though I don't see that happening with FIFA anytime soon given the state of the past few FIFAs (thanks to EA) and now the newly made investment in the UCL license.

PES thank you for the great memories : PES 2017, PES 2013, PES 2011. Those were the days when I enjoyed playing PES Till my eyes hurts. Scoring with Fernando Torres in PES 2011 was memorable, Running down the wings like CR7 in PES 2013 and cutting inside to score  like The Greatest Cristiano Ronaldo himself was pure joy. Dribbling my way through defenders and feeling like I'm Messi in PES 2017 was so much fun. 

Unfortunately, it's time to say goodbye, Goodbye to the beautiful simulation game that was PES before PES 2018, Konami you ruined everything, you ruined the only thing that kept you up as well - The gameplay. It's gone, damage is done. I'm going to FIFA,  I think a game of football is much more than just gameplay, FIFA offers much more, I will try to find something that I like and move on, for a start, I want to see how the Champions League will be represented in Career Mode. RIP PES
